    "created_at": "2016-05-14T11:48:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-14T11:48:28Z",
    "body": "@paulcbetts The problem is, the `com.apple.security.temporary-exception.sbpl` rule is a must-have for Electron, rewriting Chromium's IPC system is basically impossible work. So it makes this issue just unable to be resolved.\n\nThe only thing we can do, is to rename the `org.chromium.Chromium.rohitfork.[0-9]+` mach channel to something like `com.yourcompany.yourapp.rohitfork.[0-9]+`, but I don't know whether it makes things better or worse. We really need to know how the reviewers of Mac App Store think.\n"
  },
